parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the power steering cuts in and out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power steering, brake lights, and airbag malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The dashboard lights and gauges malfunction
the anti-theft warning light illuminates
the brake lights stay on or off
the airbag warning light stays on
and the power steering loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control and Brake Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control and brake lights can cause accidents or injuries, as the vehicle may not respond as expected, and the brake lights may not function properly.
symptoms: The cruise control stops working
the brake lights stay on or off
and the vehicle may stall or hesitate to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag and Passenger Presence Sensor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system and passenger presence sensor can cause serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the airbag may not deploy or may deploy unnecessarily.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger presence sensor defaults
and the airbag may not deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering loses power
making it difficult to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the ignition switch malfunctions
and the anti-theft system warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and shifting system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifts jerkily
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated on the dashboard
the "Service Airbag" message appears on the screen
the passenger airbag "off" light remains on
and the airbag warning light turns on and off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag "off" light remains on
the "Service Airbag" message appears on the screen
and the airbag warning light turns on and off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system to deploy in the event of a crash can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbags did not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning light remained illuminated
and the "Service Airbag" message appeared on the screen.
